  "label": "Garron Mavek",
  "description": "This individual is a broad-shouldered human guard of early middle years, marked by a heavy brow and a squared jaw shaped by hard service. Brown eyes sit deep under pronounced orbital ridges, and brown hair is kept in a shortknot to clear the face during watch duty. Bronze skin shows weathering at the cheeks and nose, with a thin, healed cut-line running from the right cheek toward the jaw hinge. The hands are thick-knuckled and callused, consistent with long practice in spear and shield drill.",
